Done. Here's a summary of the changes:

**`src/safety.rs`** — two edits:

1. **Fixed `check_reverse_shell` (lines 930-948)**: Replaced the simple `cmd_lower.contains(tool)` check with a loop that finds all occurrences of `nc `, `ncat `, and `netcat `, then verifies each match starts at a word boundary using the existing `is_at_word_boundary()`. This prevents false positives on:
   • `rsync -c /path` (contains `nc ` from `ync -c`)
   • `uncompress -c file` (contains `nc ` from `ncompress -`)
   • `grep -rnc pattern` (contains `nc ` from `rnc `)

2. **Added 6 test cases** to `test_analyze_reverse_shell`:
   • `ncat -c /bin/bash` → SHOULD trigger ✅
   • `netcat -e /bin/sh` → SHOULD trigger ✅
   • `nc -l -p 8080` → should NOT trigger (listener, no execute flag)
   • `rsync -c /path/to/files` → should NOT trigger (false positive fixed)
   • `uncompress -c archive.gz` → should NOT trigger (false positive fixed)
   • `grep -rnc 'pattern' .` → should NOT trigger (false positive fixed)
